            Six sigma stastistical quantity?
        


Walter Andrew Shewhart founded the modern science of industrial quality control by demonstrating that three sigmas from the mean is the point at which a manufacturing process requires correction, and established "Six Sigma" as a measurement standard in product variation.

To what statistical quantity...
 show more 
 Walter Andrew Shewhart founded the modern science of industrial quality control by demonstrating that three sigmas from the mean is the point at which a manufacturing process requires correction, and established "Six Sigma" as a measurement standard in product variation. 

To what statistical quantity does the term "sigma" refer?





 
