Walter A. Shewhart Quotes (6 quotes)“Postulate 1. All chance systems of causes are not alike in the sense that they enable us to predict the future in terms of the past.”  ―Walter A. ShewhartFacebookTwitterPicture“Postulate 2. Constant systems of chance causes do exist in nature.”  ―Walter A. ShewhartFacebookTwitterPicture“Postulate 3. Assignable causes of variation may be found and eliminated.”  ―Walter A. ShewhartSource/Notes:  Shewhart, Walter A. (1931). Economic control of quality of manufactured product. D. Van Nostrand Company. p. 8.FacebookTwitterPicture“In other words, the fact that the criterion we happen to use has a fine ancestry of highbrow statistical theorems does not justify its use. Such justification must come from empirical evidence that it works.”  ―Walter A. ShewhartSource/Notes:  Shewhart, Walter A. (1931). Economic control of quality of manufactured product. D. Van Nostrand Company. p. 18.FacebookTwitterPicture“Rule 1. Original data should be presented in a way that will preserve the evidence in the original data for all the predictions assumed to be useful.”  ―Walter A. ShewhartFacebookTwitterPicture“Both pure and applied science have gradually pushed further and further the requirements for accuracy and precision. However, applied science, particularly in the mass production of interchangeable parts, is even more exacting than pure science in certain matters of accuracy and precision.”  ―Walter A. ShewhartFacebookTwitterPicture


